Personal Annual Objectives – Senior Developer (Simplified)
Objective 1: Deliver Secure, High-Quality, and Resilient Solutions
Weight: 35%

Build and maintain systems that are reliable, secure, and aligned to business and risk objectives.

Key Results
KR1: Improve quality and reduce production issues
Reduce release failures and production incidents
Ensure all releases meet quality standards (testing, approvals, monitoring)
Build resilient systems with strong error handling and recovery

KR2: Embed controls and risk awareness into solutions
Implement controls within code and pipelines (validation, monitoring, alerts)
Ensure secure handling of data and compliance with standards
Support early detection of issues through effective monitoring

KR3: Deliver reliably against commitments
Deliver ≥95% of committed work on time
Accurately estimate and manage delivery of tasks
Proactively identify and escalate risks or blockers

KR4: Strengthen engineering standards and documentation
Maintain clear and up-to-date technical documentation
Ensure consistency in coding standards and best practices
Contribute to improving team processes and ways of working

------
Objective 2: Drive Efficient and Value-Focused Delivery
Weight: 45%

Lead delivery of solutions that improve performance, reduce cost, and create business value.

Key Results
KR5: Deliver transformation and migration initiatives
Contribute to key transformation programmes (e.g. cloud migration)
Ensure smooth transition from legacy to modern platforms
Support decommissioning of old systems

KR6: Improve system performance and efficiency
Reduce runtime, improve reliability, and optimise cost
Identify and implement performance improvements
Minimise operational overhead and support effort
KR7: Improve delivery efficiency

Reduce lead time from development to production
Increase automation in testing and deployment
Improve development workflows and tooling

KR8: Lead and mentor others
Support and coach junior developers
Promote best practices and high engineering standards
Contribute to building a strong team culture

----
Objective 3: Leverage AI and Automation to Improve Delivery
Weight: 20%

Use AI and automation to enhance productivity, quality, and innovation.

Key Results
KR9: Increase adoption of AI tools
Use approved AI tools to support development (coding, testing, documentation)
Improve speed and quality of delivery using AI

KR10: Deliver efficiency through automation
Automate repetitive development and operational tasks
Improve quality through automated checks and validation
Demonstrate measurable improvements in productivity or reliability
Overall Focus Areas for a Senior Developer
High-quality, secure, and resilient systems
Reliable and predictable delivery
Performance and cost optimisation
Technical leadership and mentoring
Continuous improvement and automation
Effective use of AI and modern engineering tools
